From Jim De Arras Subject Re My Gun is like my American Express Card In article CMM Thomas Parsli writes Observations from a naive norwegian Guns are made to KILL people not to shoot target or to have something more macho than stamps to It IS more easy to kill injure someone with a gun than with a knife or a bat as in baseball It's not very wise to compare two completely different countries like USA and let's say Island on issues like crime and Yes the problem is people committing crimes not the tools beeing used but should be taken into Only as far as it affects the crime We have a very strict gun legislation in Norway but until recently it was possible for enyone over years to buy a Shotguns are used mainly for hunting in Norway but because it was so easy to accuire one it was THE most used gun in The solution was to restrict the sale so it's now necessary to apply and register your And unbelievable the use of guns in crime Did the RATE of crime fall If not the ban was of no It is the rate of violent crime that matters not the tools It's the crime stupid There are now a new law against wearing long knives in public and why should it be allowed Apparently that became the weapon of choice after the shotguns were After that they'll decide the car of choice is the Saab and propose a ban on that What I as an scandinavian have problems to understand is that you Americans have a more liberal view on guns and violence than on nudity and Try showing a bare breast on tv insted of violence and Yes I know a little American history but is it a civil human right to have an assault gun in your home and or an handgun in your car We still trust honest people For the time The bad english is not my fault it's probably the keyboard software or the quality of the subtext on Disclamer not These are the views of all studens at my university all Norwegians and probably whole of the Thomas Parsli I'm always rethinking There's never been a day when I haven't rethought But I can't do that b